post_text:
Below are links to our Virtual Graduation Videos. They will be made live May 26th at 6:00 pm. Please see our website for more information: https://vhs.davis.k12.ut.us/

The first link is to a high school landing page that is accessible through each high school web page. The video there can be stopped, started, and scrubbed forward or backward.
https://vhs.davis.k12.ut.us/school-information/virtual-graduation-2020

The second link is to the high school's official YouTube page. The video there can also be stopped, started, and scrubbed forward or backward.
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCOc0EtlNfVTQQ895M-Ms6Gw

The third link is to Deseret Digital Media. This video will be played "live," but doesn't have the capability to be stopped or scrubbed forward or backward.
https://watchit.ksl.com/embed/event/_/1cdmku8

Again, these will be accessible on May 26th at 6:00 pm.

post_text: We finally have yearbook news, and it's not what any of us wanted to hear. Due to COVID-19 and subsequent business closures we will not be able to distribute yearbooks until the week of June 15th. We are so sorry! More details on distribution times will be forthcoming.

post_text: Viking Nation will honor our Seniors on Wednesday, May 20th. Tune in live @vick_the_viking on Instagram live beginning at 8:50 pm. We will begin with prerecorded messages from the senior class officers followed by the lighting of our football field lights at 9:00 pm. The live portion will last about 5 minutes, but the lights will remain on until 10:00 pm. Please participate online. Do not come to the school.

It‚Äôs Here! Viking Preview is tonight, Thursday, February 8th at 6:00 PM in the VHS Big Gym.
The evening starts with a presentation covering class selection, earning college credit, and how to get the most out of your high school experience. Course request materials for incoming students will be available after this session.
Teachers will hold break-out sessions about their classes as well as an Open House where Counselors, Teachers, Clubs Advisors and Coaches will be available to answer your questions and provide helpful information about courses offered at Viewmont.

Students at Viewmont High School raised over $76,000. Some of that money went to purchase Christmas for every student at Vae View Elementary. Volunteers delivered the surprise Wednesday morning. Read what other schools did in the spirt of giving at http://www.davis.k12.ut.us/Page/99926
